  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="tint">
    <header>
      <h1>HelloTrello!</h1>
      <p>
        This site is populated with content from a public <a href="https://trello.com/b/Zzc0USwZ/hellotrello">Trello board</a>. Every deployment pulls the  content from the Trello API and generates the site's HTML at build time on <a href="https://netlify.com">Netlify</a>.
      </p>
    </header>
  </div>
  <main>
    {% for card in cards %}
    <section>
      <h2>{{ card.name }} </h2>
      <div>
      {% markdown %}
        {{- card.desc }}
      {% endmarkdown %}
      </div>
    </section>
    {% endfor %}
  </main>
  <div class="tint">
    <footer>
      <p>
        This example includes <a href="https://stage--hellotrello.netlify.app">staging</a> and <a href="https://hellotrello.netlify.app">production</a> examples. These are poswere by Netlify's Brach Deploys, but the code on each bracng is identical. They filter the content ioncluded based on the labels on the trello cards and the branch name.
      </p>
      <p>
        Check out the <a href="{{ pkg.repository.url }}">code in GitHub</a> to learn more and try this out for yourself.
      </p>
    </footer>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
